    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-11-20T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-11-20T04:00:00-05:00" n="858"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d858">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/11–2050: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Korea</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Muccio</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-11-20T18:00:00+09:00"
                            >November 20, 1950—6 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 20—8:56 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>412. Two Chinese prisoners referred to in <gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 408, November 19 as taken by the US 24th Division were found
                    on interrogation to be from CC 117th Division. <gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                        >ROK</gloss> Chief of Staff and <gloss target="#t_G21">G–2</gloss> state
                    that during past few days 87 Chinese have been captured in <gloss
                        target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> Second Corps area. Good portion of these
                    prisoners are said to be from CC 42nd Army, including lieutenant who asserted he
                    from CC 124th Division. Foregoing <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> reports
                    should be accepted with reserve pending clarification.</p>
                <p>Statement in <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 208 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >408</hi>] there no hostile air activity 18th over North Korea is erroneous.
                    Delayed report from Navy which conducted operations along Yalu 18th states Navy
                    craft clashed with at least 14 Mig jets, of which 1 was shot down and 3 damaged.
                    Eighth Army states there was no hostile air activity over North Korea
                    yesterday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Muccio</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
